  "title": "Riptide Guardian",
  "secondName": "Riptide Guardian",
  "description": "When the first Dragon of Water was slain by the Eternal, he gifted Kaidaros his power, and she used it well. It was not she who brought warfare and corruption to the sea. It was the humans, and their greed.\n\nTheir crafts started plain, barely anything more than hollow logs on the water. But as they grew ever more prideful and sailed ever further, they slew one another on her waters, hunted her ocean's bounty until entire species died. She could allow it no longer.\n\nHer waves ripped mast from hull and dragged the villainous men to her depths. For generations, she pushed them back to their shores, until no one dared venture forth into the sea.\n\nNo one, that is, but the people who looked at her waters with awe, not avarice.",
